        Your psireport gives you the necessary information that you need
to make decisions in how and when to advance your character.  There is
more to the Psionicist Guild than simply earning XP.  This will explain
what information the psireport gives, and how you can make use of it.
 
First is your psionic profile.  This is the description by which other
psionicists know you, and is what appears in the 'psions' list.  You
may alter this through use of the Psionic Profile power.
 
Your guild experience points control when you are eligible to advance
your guild level.  It is not enough to merely earn the experience
required, you must also spend some time at each guild level getting to
know your powers.  Each time you use a power that costs an amount
equal to your current Guild Level or more, you earn 1 or more guild
experience points.  The more spell points you spend, the more guild
experience you earn.
 
Your psionic powers total and psionic potential total tell you how many
points you have spent on powers and how many you still have left.  You
will gain 7 points of psionic potential for each Guild Level you
advance, including the first one.
 
Your Psychic Reserve lists how many points you have currently in your
reserve to the left of the slash, and how many maximum you can have to
the right.  See the Psychic Reserve power description for details.
 
Lastly, your psireport maintains 3 lists of powers for you.  The first
is simply a list of the powers you currently possess.  Your mastered
powers are those you have used Power Mastery on to increase your
abilities.  See the Power Mastery power description for details.  The
last, Eligible Powers, is a list provided for your convenience of the
powers you can currently purchase using the 'learn' command at the guild
or the Enlightenment power.
